-- Morley's Theorem Structure (Area Method)
-- This file demonstrates the Area Method syntax for the General Case.
-- Note: Requires EL5 (PointInterAng) implementation to return non-placeholder values.

-- 1. Base Triangle (Equilateral PQR)
:construct (Q free)
:construct (R free)
-- P makes 60 deg with QR and RQ. tan(60) = s.
-- (- 0 s) represents negative s
:construct (P inter_ang Q R s R Q (- 0 s))

-- 2. Construct Vertex A
-- Angle at Q: 60 + beta. Tangent tQ.
-- Angle at R: 120 - gamma. Tangent tR.
:construct (A inter_ang Q R tQ R Q tR)

-- 3. Construct Vertex B
-- Angle at R: 180 - gamma?
-- Angle at P: ...
:construct (B inter_ang R P tRB P R tPB)

-- 4. Goal
-- Prove AB makes correct angle.
:prove-area (S A B P)